The paper focuses on representation learning for remote sensing datasets, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the importance of dataset characteristics and evaluation protocols, which suggests relevance to information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) sub-categories such as cs.IR and cs.CL. Finally, the paper uses deep learning models, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well.
